text.tspan: The Grand Hotel Infinita is a place where the rooms never end and the
When the most cherished possessions of the guests vanish without a
trace, panic spreads through the lobby. How can Anne and her clever
Border collie, Scotch, find a missing pipe or a lost monocle in a hotel
with an infinite number of rooms and floors? It seems like an
impossible problem, but Anne and Scotch are about to discover that
even a paradox can have a perfectly logical solution.
